<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
I started with the mushroom quest, but I was high level already.  Accidently stumbled onto one of the dogs, who died instantly.  I knew I had the Crumpled Scroll of Mass Resurrection, so I killed all the dogs, and got the mushrooms in peace. <p>
Then BEFORE I approached Maggot, I read the scroll.  Yet he still called me a murderer etc. 
</p>
<p>
I don't know if this is a bug, because then maybe I'd have to redo the Eol quest too, but I thought that would've saved me from a failed quest. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: All uniques that are generated in quests, special levels, etc. (those with the SPECIAL_GENE flag) are not resurrected by the scroll. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: So just to make it clear, it's not a bug.  Having tried to revive them doesn't un-do the fact that you did murder them. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./ReenenLaurie">ReenenLaurie</a>:  Awwww... you make me sound so EVIL... <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15">   But I guess you're right  (I think I moved it to resolved). 
</p>
